Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu briefs the media on the outcomes of a cabinet meeting. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. PRETORIA - Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu will brief the media on the outcomes of a cabinet meeting held on Wednesday. The issues expected to be raised are the state of the economy and the National Health Insurance Bill. READ: Health Minister confident in NHI President Cyril Ramaphosa is also back in court with public protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane bringing an interdict against her. As questions mount about the scandals playing out in the public domain, the government is under pressure to address these concerns.